tr.td:
        The operator must be on a new line. For example:

someVariable = aBigVariableNameToMakeThings + "this may work"
               + lookVeryInteresting;

        The operator must be at the end of the line. For example:

someVariable = aBigVariableNameToMakeThings + "this may work" +
               lookVeryInteresting;

        Require that there is some text in the block. For example:

catch (Exception ex) {
    // This is a bad coding practice
}

        Require that there is a statement in the block. For example:

finally {
    lock.release();
}

        The brace must always be on the end of the line. For example:

if (condition) {
    ...

        The brace must always be on a new line. For example:

if (condition)
{
    ...

        The brace must be on the same line as the next statement. For
        example:

try {
    ...
} finally {

        The brace must be alone on the line. For example:

try {
    ...
}
finally {

All static imports are at the top. For example:

    import static a.b.C.*;
    import static x.y.Z.*;

    import a.b.D;
    import x.y.Z;

All static imports are above the local group.. For example:

    import static a.b.C.*;
    import a.b.D;

    import static x.y.Z.*;
    import x.y.Z;

All static imports are processed like non static
              imports. For example:

    import static a.b.C.*;
    import a.b.D;

    import x.y.Z;
    import static x.y.Z.*;

All static imports are under the local group. For example:

    import a.b.D;
    import static a.b.C.*;

    import x.y.Z;
    import static x.y.Z.*;

All static imports are at the bottom. For example:

    import a.b.D;
    import x.y.Z;

    import static a.b.C.*;
    import static x.y.Z.*;
